info.name: Stockast
info.description:
Stockast API definitions.

All requests (except for new-user creation) require Authentication.

Stockast uses Basic Authentication as described [here](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Basic_access_authentication#Client_side).

Basic authentication consists includding an `Authorization` header with the value being `Basic <hash>`.
The `<hash>` consists of the base64 encoded string: `username:password` (note the `:` between username and password).


Example:

- Username: `someone@example.com`
- Password: `1234`
- Hash of `someone@example.com:1234`: `c29tZW9uZUBleGFtcGxlLmNvbToxMjM0`
- Basic Authentication Header:
```
Authorization: Basic c29tZW9uZUBleGFtcGxlLmNvbToxMjM0
```
